112static const char *starts_with(const char *big, const char *little)
113{
114 while (*little) {
115 if (*little++ != *big++) {
116 return NULL;
117 }
118 }
119 return big;
120}
121
122static void skip_whitespace(const char **line)
123{
124 while (isspace(**line)) {
125 (*line)++;
126 }
127}
128
129static void skip_whitespace2(char **line)
130{
131 while (isspace(**line)) {
132 (*line)++;
133 }
134}
135
136static const char *matches(const char *line, const char *directive)
137{
138 skip_whitespace(&line);
139
140 if (*line == '.') {
141 line = starts_with(line + 1, directive);
142 if (line && (!*line || isspace(*line))) {
143 skip_whitespace(&line);
144 return line;
145 }
146 }
147
148 return NULL;
149}
150
151static int unquote(const char *arg, char *to, size_t to_size, char q, char expected, const char **remainder)
152{
153 const char *quote;
154 const char *end;
155 size_t len;
156
157 skip_whitespace(&arg);
158 if (*arg != q) {
159 return -1;
160 }
161
162 arg++;
163
164 end = arg;
165 do {
166 quote = strchr(end, q);
167 if (!quote) {
168 return -2;
169 }
170 end = quote + 1;
171 } while (*(quote - 1) == '\\');
172
173 skip_whitespace(&end);
174 if (*end != expected) {
175 return -3;
176 }
177
178 if (remainder) {
179 *remainder = end + 1;
180 }
181
182 len = (size_t) (quote - arg);
183 if (len >= to_size) {
184 return -4;
185 }
186
187 strncpy(to, arg, len);
188 to[len] = '\0';
189
190 return (int) len;
191}

193/* Line-reading. */
194
195static char *read_line_from_file(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, FILE *file)
196{
197 int bufsize = BSIZE;
198 char *buf;
199 char *p;
200
201 buf = yasm_xmalloc((size_t)bufsize);
202
203 /* Loop to ensure entire line is read (don't want to limit line length). */
204 p = buf;
205 for (;;) {
206 if (!fgets(p, bufsize - (p - buf), file)) {
207 if (ferror(file)) {
208 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_IO, N_("error when reading from file"));
209 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
210 }
211 break;
212 }
213 p += strlen(p);
214 if (p > buf && p[-1] == '\n') {
215 break;
216 }
217 if ((p - buf) + 1 >= bufsize) {
218 /* Increase size of buffer */
219 char *oldbuf = buf;
220 bufsize *= 2;
221 buf = yasm_xrealloc(buf, (size_t) bufsize);
222 p = buf + (p - oldbuf);
223 }
224 }
225
226 if (p == buf) {
227 /* No data; must be at EOF */
228 yasm_xfree(buf);
229 return NULL;
230 }
231
232 /* Strip the line ending */
233 buf[strcspn(buf, "\r\n")] = '\0';
234 return buf;
235}
236
237static char *read_line(yasm_preproc_gas *pp)
238{
239 char *line;
240
241 if (!SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->included_files)) {
242 included_file *inc_file = SLIST_FIRST(&pp->included_files);
243 if (inc_file->lines_remaining <= 0) {
244 SLIST_REMOVE_HEAD(&pp->included_files, next);
245 yasm_xfree(inc_file->filename);
246 yasm_xfree(inc_file);
247 }
248 }
249
250 if (!SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->buffered_lines)) {
251 buffered_line *bline = SLIST_FIRST(&pp->buffered_lines);
252 SLIST_REMOVE_HEAD(&pp->buffered_lines, next);
253 line = bline->line;
254 if (bline->line_number != -1) {
255 pp->next_line_number = bline->line_number;
256 }
257 yasm_xfree(bline);
258 if (!SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->included_files)) {
259 SLIST_FIRST(&pp->included_files)->lines_remaining--;
260 }
261 return line;
262 }
263
264 line = read_line_from_file(pp, pp->in);
265 if (line) {
266 pp->in_line_number++;
267 pp->next_line_number = pp->in_line_number;
268 }
269
270 return line;
271}
272
273static const char *get_arg(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, const char *src, char *dest, size_t dest_size)
274{
275 const char *comma = strchr(src, ',');
276 if (comma) {
277 size_t len = (size_t) (comma - src);
278 if (len >= dest_size) {
279 len = dest_size - 1;
280 }
281 strncpy(dest, src, len);
282 dest[len] = '\0';
283 comma++;
284 skip_whitespace(&comma);
285 } else {
286 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("expected comma"));
287 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
288 }
289 return comma;
290}

294static char get_char(yasm_preproc_gas *pp)
295{
296 return pp->expr.string[pp->expr.string_cursor];
297}

299static const char *get_str(yasm_preproc_gas *pp)
300{
301 return pp->expr.string + pp->expr.string_cursor;
302}
303
304static void next_char(yasm_preproc_gas *pp)
305{
306 pp->expr.string_cursor++;
307}

309static int ishex(char c)
310{
311 c = tolower(c);
312 return isdigit(c) || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f');
313}
314
315static void gas_scan_init(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, struct tokenval *tokval, const char *arg1)
316{
317 pp->expr.symbol = NULL;
318 pp->expr.string = arg1;
319 pp->expr.string_cursor = 0;
320 memset(tokval, 0, sizeof(struct tokenval));
321 tokval->t_type = TOKEN_INVALID;
322}
323
324static void gas_scan_cleanup(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, struct tokenval *tokval)
325{
326 if (tokval->t_integer) {
327 yasm_intnum_destroy(tokval->t_integer);
328 tokval->t_integer = NULL;
329 }
330 if (pp->expr.symbol) {
331 yasm_xfree(pp->expr.symbol);
332 pp->expr.symbol = NULL;
333 }
334}
335
336static int gas_scan(void *preproc, struct tokenval *tokval)
337{
338 yasm_preproc_gas *pp = (yasm_preproc_gas *) preproc;
339 char c = get_char(pp);
340 const char *str;
341
342 tokval->t_charptr = NULL;
343
344 if (c == '\0') {
345 return tokval->t_type = TOKEN_EOS;
346 }
347
348 if (isspace(c)) {
349 do {
350 next_char(pp);
351 c = get_char(pp);
352 } while (isspace(c));
353 }
354
355 if (isdigit(c)) {
356 int char_index = 0;
357 int value = 0;
358
359 do {
360 value = value*10 + (c - '0');
361 char_index++;
362 next_char(pp);
363 c = get_char(pp);
364 if (char_index == 1 && c == 'x' && value == 0) {
365 next_char(pp);
366 c = get_char(pp);
367 /* Hex notation. */
368 while (ishex(c)) {
369 if (isdigit(c)) {
370 value = (value << 4) | (c - '0');
371 } else {
372 value = (value << 4) | (tolower(c) - 'a' + 0xa);
373 }
374 next_char(pp);
375 c = get_char(pp);
376 }
377 break;
378 }
379 } while (isdigit(c));
380
381 if (tokval->t_integer) {
382 yasm_intnum_destroy(tokval->t_integer);
383 }
384 tokval->t_integer = yasm_intnum_create_int(value);
385 return tokval->t_type = TOKEN_NUM;
386 }
387
388 tokval->t_type = TOKEN_INVALID;
389 str = get_str(pp);
390
391 {
392 /* It should be tested whether GAS supports all of these or if there are missing ones. */
393 unsigned i;
394 struct {
395 const char *op;
396 int token;
397 } ops[] = {
398 { "<<", TOKEN_SHL },
399 { ">>", TOKEN_SHR },
400 { "//", TOKEN_SDIV },
401 { "%%", TOKEN_SMOD },
402 { "==", TOKEN_EQ },
403 { "!=", TOKEN_NE },
404 { "<>", TOKEN_NE },
405 { "<>", TOKEN_NE },
406 { "<=", TOKEN_LE },
407 { ">=", TOKEN_GE },
408 { "&&", TOKEN_DBL_AND },
409 { "^^", TOKEN_DBL_XOR },
410 { "||", TOKEN_DBL_OR }
411 };
412 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(ops)/sizeof(ops[0]); i++) {
413 if (!strcmp(str, ops[i].op)) {
414 tokval->t_type = ops[i].token;
415 break;
416 }
417 }
418 }
419
420 if (tokval->t_type != TOKEN_INVALID) {
421 next_char(pp);
422 next_char(pp);
423 } else {
424 str = get_str(pp);
425
426 next_char(pp);
427 tokval->t_type = c;
428
429 /* Is it a symbol? If so we need to make it a TOKEN_ID. */
430 if (isalpha(c) || c == '_' || c == '.') {
431 int symbol_length = 1;
432
433 c = get_char(pp);
434 while (isalnum(c) || c == '$' || c == '_') {
435 symbol_length++;
436 next_char(pp);
437 c = get_char(pp);
438 }
439
440 pp->expr.symbol = yasm_xrealloc(pp->expr.symbol, symbol_length + 1);
441 memcpy(pp->expr.symbol, str, symbol_length);
442 pp->expr.symbol[symbol_length] = '\0';
443
444 tokval->t_type = TOKEN_ID;
445 tokval->t_charptr = pp->expr.symbol;
446 }
447 }
448
449 return tokval->t_type;
450}
451
452static void gas_err(void *private_data, int severity, const char *fmt, ...)
453{
454 va_list args;
455 yasm_preproc_gas *pp = private_data;
456
457 if (!pp->detect_errors_only) {
458 va_start(args, fmt);
459 yasm_error_set_va(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_(fmt), args);
460 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
461 va_end(args);
462 }
463
464 pp->fatal_error = 1;
465}
466
467static long eval_expr(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, const char *arg1)
468{
469 struct tokenval tv;
470 yasm_expr *expr;
471 yasm_intnum *intn;
472 long value;
473 expr_state prev_state;
474
475 if (!*arg1) {
476 return 0;
477 }
478
479 prev_state = pp->expr;
480 gas_scan_init(pp, &tv, arg1);
481 expr = evaluate(gas_scan, pp, &tv, pp, CRITICAL, gas_err, pp->defines);
482 intn = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&expr, 0);
483 value = yasm_intnum_get_int(intn);
484 yasm_expr_destroy(expr);
485 gas_scan_cleanup(pp, &tv);
486 pp->expr = prev_state;
487
488 return value;
489}

491/* If-directive helpers. */
492
493static int handle_if(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int is_true)
494{
495 assert(pp->depth >= 0);
496 assert(pp->skip_depth == 0);
497 if (is_true) {
498 pp->depth++;
499 } else {
500 pp->skip_depth = 1;
501 }
502 return 1;
503}
504
505static int handle_endif(yasm_preproc_gas *pp)
506{
507 if (pp->depth) {
508 pp->depth--;
509 } else {
510 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("\".endif\" without \".if\""));
511 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
512 return 0;
513 }
514 return 1;
515}
516
517static int handle_else(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int is_elseif)
518{
519 if (!pp->depth) {
520 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("\".%s\" without \".if\""), is_elseif ? "elseif" : "else");
521 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
522 return 0;
523 } else {
524 pp->skip_depth = 1;
525 }
526 return 1;
527}
528
529/* Directive-handling functions. */
530
531static int eval_if(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int negate, const char *arg1)
532{
533 long value;
534 if (!*arg1) {
535 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("expression is required in \".if\" statement"));
536 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
537 return 0;
538 }
539 value = eval_expr(pp, arg1);
540 handle_if(pp, (negate ? !value : !!value));
541 return 1;
542}
543
544static int eval_else(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused)
545{
546 return handle_else(pp, 0);
547}
548
549static int eval_endif(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused)
550{
551 return handle_endif(pp);
552}
553
554static int eval_elseif(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused, const char *arg1)
555{
556 if (!*arg1) {
557 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("expression is required in \".elseif\" statement"));
558 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
559 return 0;
560 }
561 if (!handle_else(pp, 1)) {
562 return 0;
563 }
564 return eval_if(pp, 0, arg1);
565}
566
567static int eval_ifb(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int negate, const char *arg1)
568{
569 int is_blank = !*arg1;
570 return handle_if(pp, (negate ? !is_blank : is_blank));
571}
572
573static int eval_ifc(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int negate, const char *args)
574{
575 char arg1[512], arg2[512];
576 const char *remainder;
577 int len = unquote(args, arg1, sizeof(arg1), '\'', ',', &remainder);
578 if (len >= 0) {
579 len = unquote(remainder, arg2, sizeof(arg2), '\'', '\0', NULL);
580 if (len >= 0) {
581 int result = !strcmp(arg1, arg2);
582 return handle_if(pp, (negate ? !result : result));
583 }
584 } else {
585 /* first argument was not single-quoted, assume non-quoted mode */
586 remainder = get_arg(pp, args, arg1, sizeof(arg1));
587 if (remainder) {
588 int result = !strcmp(arg1, remainder);
589 return handle_if(pp, (negate ? !result : result));
590 }
591 }
592 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("\"%s\" expects two single-quoted or unquoted arguments"), negate ? ".ifnc" : ".ifc");
593 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
594 return 0;
595}
596
597static int eval_ifeqs(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int negate, const char *args)
598{
599 char arg1[512], arg2[512];
600 const char *remainder;
601 int len = unquote(args, arg1, sizeof(arg1), '"', ',', &remainder);
602 if (len >= 0) {
603 len = unquote(remainder, arg2, sizeof(arg2), '"', '\0', NULL);
604 if (len >= 0) {
605 int result = !strcmp(arg1, arg2);
606 return handle_if(pp, (negate ? !result : result));
607 }
608 }
609 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("\"%s\" expects two double-quoted arguments"), negate ? ".ifnes" : ".ifeqs");
610 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
611 return 1;
612}

614static int eval_ifdef(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int negate, const char *name)
615{
616 yasm_symrec *rec = yasm_symtab_get(pp->defines, name);
617 int result = (rec != NULL);
618 return handle_if(pp, (negate ? !result : result));
619}

621static int eval_ifge(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int negate, const char *arg1)
622{
623 long value = eval_expr(pp, arg1);
624 int result = (value >= 0);
625 return handle_if(pp, (negate ? !result : result));
626}

628static int eval_ifgt(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int negate, const char *arg1)
629{
630 long value = eval_expr(pp, arg1);
631 int result = (value > 0);
632 return handle_if(pp, (negate ? !result : result));
633}
634
635static int eval_include(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused, const char *arg1)
636{
637 char *current_filename;
638 char filename[MAXPATHLEN];
639 char *line;
640 int num_lines;
641 FILE *file;
642 buffered_line *prev_bline;
643 included_file *inc_file;
644
645 if (unquote(arg1, filename, sizeof(filename), '"', '\0', NULL) < 0) {
646 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("string expected"));
647 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
648 return 0;
649 }
650
651 if (SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->included_files)) {
652 current_filename = pp->in_filename;
653 } else {
654 current_filename = SLIST_FIRST(&pp->included_files)->filename;
655 }
656 file = yasm_fopen_include(filename, current_filename, "r", NULL);
657 if (!file) {
658 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("unable to open included file \"%s\""), filename);
659 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
660 return 0;
661 }
662
663 num_lines = 0;
664 prev_bline = NULL;
665 line = read_line_from_file(pp, file);
666 while (line) {
667 buffered_line *bline = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(buffered_line));
668 bline->line = line;
669 bline->line_number = -1;
670 if (prev_bline) {
671 SLIST_INSERT_AFTER(prev_bline, bline, next);
672 } else {
673 SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&pp->buffered_lines, bline, next);
674 }
675 prev_bline = bline;
676 line = read_line_from_file(pp, file);
677 num_lines++;
678 }
679
680 inc_file = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(included_file));
681 inc_file->filename = yasm__xstrdup(filename);
682 inc_file->lines_remaining = num_lines;
683 SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&pp->included_files, inc_file, next);
684 return 1;
685}
686
687static int try_eval_expr(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, const char *value, long *result)
688{
689 int success;
690
691 pp->detect_errors_only = 1;
692 *result = eval_expr(pp, value);
693 success = !pp->fatal_error;
694 pp->fatal_error = 0;
695 pp->detect_errors_only = 0;
696
697 return success;
698}
699
700static int remove_define(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, const char *name, int allow_redefine)
701{
702 yasm_symrec *rec = yasm_symtab_get(pp->defines, name);
703 if (rec) {
704 const yasm_symtab_iter *entry;
705 yasm_symtab *new_defines;
706
707 if (!allow_redefine) {
708 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("symbol \"%s\" is already defined"), name);
709 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
710 return 0;
711 }
712
713 new_defines = yasm_symtab_create();
714
715 for (entry = yasm_symtab_first(pp->defines); entry; entry = yasm_symtab_next(entry)) {
716 yasm_symrec *entry_rec = yasm_symtab_iter_value(entry);
717 const char *rec_name = yasm_symrec_get_name(entry_rec);
718 if (strcmp(rec_name, name)) {
719 yasm_intnum *num = yasm_intnum_create_int(eval_expr(pp, rec_name));
720 yasm_expr *expr = yasm_expr_create_ident(yasm_expr_int(num), 0);
721 yasm_symtab_define_equ(new_defines, rec_name, expr, 0);
722 }
723 }
724
725 yasm_symtab_destroy(pp->defines);
726 pp->defines = new_defines;
727 }
728 return (rec != NULL);
729}
730
731static void add_define(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, const char *name, long value, int allow_redefine, int substitute)
732{
733 deferred_define *def, *prev_def, *temp_def;
734 yasm_intnum *num;
735 yasm_expr *expr;
736
737 remove_define(pp, name, allow_redefine);
738
739 /* Add the new define. */
740 num = yasm_intnum_create_int(value);
741 expr = yasm_expr_create_ident(yasm_expr_int(num), 0);
742 yasm_symtab_define_equ(pp->defines, name, expr, 0);
743
744 /* Perform substitution on any deferred defines. */
745 if (substitute) {
746 prev_def = NULL;
747 temp_def = NULL;
748 SLIST_FOREACH_SAFE(def, &pp->deferred_defines, next, temp_def) {
749 if (substitute_values(pp, &def->value)) {
750 /* Value was updated - check if it can be added to the symtab. */
751 if (try_eval_expr(pp, def->value, &value)) {
752 add_define(pp, def->name, value, FALSE, FALSE);
753 if (prev_def) {
754 SLIST_NEXT(prev_def, next) = SLIST_NEXT(def, next);
755 } else {
756 SLIST_FIRST(&pp->deferred_defines) = SLIST_NEXT(def, next);
757 }
758 yasm_xfree(def->name);
759 yasm_xfree(def->value);
760 yasm_xfree(def);
761 continue;
762 }
763 }
764 prev_def = def;
765 }
766 }
767}
768
769static int eval_set(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int allow_redefine, const char *name, const char *value)
770{
771 if (!pp->skip_depth) {
772 long result;
773
774 if (!try_eval_expr(pp, value, &result)) {
775 deferred_define *def;
776 remove_define(pp, name, allow_redefine);
777 def = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(deferred_define));
778 def->name = yasm__xstrdup(name);
779 def->value = yasm__xstrdup(value);
780 substitute_values(pp, &def->value);
781 SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&pp->deferred_defines, def, next);
782 } else {
783 add_define(pp, name, result, allow_redefine, TRUE);
784 }
785 }
786 return 1;
787}
788
789static int eval_macro(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused, char *args)
790{
791 char *end;
792 char *line;
793 long nesting = 1;
794 macro_entry *macro = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(macro_entry));
795
796 memset(macro, 0, sizeof(macro_entry));
797
798 end = args;
799 while (*end && !isspace(*end)) {
800 end++;
801 }
802 macro->name = yasm_xmalloc(end - args + 1);
803 memcpy(macro->name, args, end - args);
804 macro->name[end - args] = '\0';
805
806 skip_whitespace2(&end);
807 while (*end) {
808 args = end;
809 while (*end && !isspace(*end) && *end != ',') {
810 end++;
811 }
812 macro->num_params++;
813 macro->params = yasm_xrealloc(macro->params, macro->num_params*sizeof(char *));
814 macro->params[macro->num_params - 1] = yasm_xmalloc(end - args + 1);
815 memcpy(macro->params[macro->num_params - 1], args, end - args);
816 macro->params[macro->num_params - 1][end - args] = '\0';
817 skip_whitespace2(&end);
818 if (*end == ',') {
819 end++;
820 skip_whitespace2(&end);
821 }
822 }
823
824 STAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&pp->macros, macro, next);
825
826 line = read_line(pp);
827 while (line) {
828 char *line2 = line;
829 skip_whitespace2(&line2);
830 if (starts_with(line2, ".macro")) {
831 nesting++;
832 } else if (starts_with(line, ".endm") && --nesting == 0) {
833 return 1;
834 }
835 macro->num_lines++;
836 macro->lines = yasm_xrealloc(macro->lines, macro->num_lines*sizeof(char *));
837 macro->lines[macro->num_lines - 1] = line;
838 line = read_line(pp);
839 }
840
841 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("unexpected EOF in \".macro\" block"));
842 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, yasm_linemap_get_current(pp->cur_lm));
843 return 0;
844}
845
846static int eval_endm(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused)
847{
848 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("\".endm\" without \".macro\""));
849 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, yasm_linemap_get_current(pp->cur_lm));
850 return 0;
851}
852
853static void get_param_value(macro_entry *macro, int param_index, const char *args, const char **value, int *length)
854{
855 int arg_index = 0;
856 const char *default_value = NULL;
857 const char *end, *eq = strstr(macro->params[param_index], "=");
858
859 if (eq) {
860 default_value = eq + 1;
861 }
862
863 skip_whitespace(&args);
864 end = args;
865 while (*end) {
866 args = end;
867 while (*end && !isspace(*end) && *end != ',') {
868 end++;
869 }
870 if (arg_index == param_index) {
871 if (end == args && default_value) {
872 *value = default_value;
873 *length = strlen(default_value);
874 } else {
875 *value = args;
876 *length = end - args;
877 }
878 return;
879 }
880 arg_index++;
881 skip_whitespace(&end);
882 if (*end == ',') {
883 end++;
884 skip_whitespace(&end);
885 }
886 }
887
888 *value = default_value;
889 *length = (default_value ? strlen(default_value) : 0);
890}
891
892static void expand_macro(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, macro_entry *macro, const char *args)
893{
894 int i, j;
895 buffered_line *prev_bline = NULL;
896
897 for (i = 0; i < macro->num_lines; i++) {
898 buffered_line *bline = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(buffered_line));
899 struct tokenval tokval;
900 int prev_was_backslash = FALSE;
901 int line_length = strlen(macro->lines[i]);
902 char *work = yasm__xstrdup(macro->lines[i]);
903 expr_state prev_state = pp->expr;
904
905 gas_scan_init(pp, &tokval, work);
906 while (gas_scan(pp, &tokval) != TOKEN_EOS) {
907 if (prev_was_backslash) {
908 if (tokval.t_type == TOKEN_ID) {
909 for (j = 0; j < macro->num_params; j++) {
910 char *end = strstr(macro->params[j], "=");
911 int len = (end ? (size_t)(end - macro->params[j])
912 : strlen(macro->params[j]));
913 if (!strncmp(tokval.t_charptr, macro->params[j], len)
914 && tokval.t_charptr[len] == '\0') {
915 /* now, find matching argument. */
916 const char *value;
917 char *line = work + (pp->expr.string - work);
918 int cursor = pp->expr.string_cursor;
919 int value_length, delta;
920
921 get_param_value(macro, j, args, &value, &value_length);
922
923 len++; /* leading slash */
924 delta = value_length - len;
925 line_length += delta;
926 if (delta > 0) {
927 line = yasm_xrealloc(line, line_length + 1);
928 }
929 memmove(line + cursor - len + value_length, line + cursor, strlen(line + cursor) + 1);
930 memcpy(line + cursor - len, value, value_length);
931 pp->expr.string = work = line;
932 pp->expr.string_cursor += delta;
933 if (pp->expr.symbol) {
934 yasm_xfree(pp->expr.symbol);
935 pp->expr.symbol = NULL;
936 }
937 }
938 }
939 }
940 prev_was_backslash = FALSE;
941 } else if (tokval.t_type == '\\') {
942 prev_was_backslash = TRUE;
943 }
944 }
945 gas_scan_cleanup(pp, &tokval);
946
947 bline->line = work + (pp->expr.string - work);
948 bline->line_number = -1;
949 pp->expr = prev_state;
950
951 if (prev_bline) {
952 SLIST_INSERT_AFTER(prev_bline, bline, next);
953 } else {
954 SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&pp->buffered_lines, bline, next);
955 }
956 prev_bline = bline;
957 }
958}
959
960static int eval_rept(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused, const char *arg1)
961{
962 long i, n = eval_expr(pp, arg1);
963 long num_lines = 0;
964 long nesting = 1;
965 char *line = read_line(pp);
966 buffered_line *prev_bline = NULL;
967 SLIST_HEAD(buffered_lines_head, buffered_line) lines;
968 int rept_start_file_line_number = pp->next_line_number - 1;
969 int rept_start_output_line_number = pp->current_line_number;
970
971 SLIST_INIT(&lines);
972
973 while (line) {
974 skip_whitespace2(&line);
975 if (starts_with(line, ".rept")) {
976 nesting++;
977 } else if (starts_with(line, ".endr") && --nesting == 0) {
978 for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
979 buffered_line *current_line;
980 prev_bline = NULL;
981 SLIST_FOREACH(current_line, &lines, next) {
982 buffered_line *bline = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(buffered_line));
983 bline->line = yasm__xstrdup(current_line->line);
984 bline->line_number = current_line->line_number;
985 if (prev_bline) {
986 SLIST_INSERT_AFTER(prev_bline, bline, next);
987 } else {
988 SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&pp->buffered_lines, bline, next);
989 }
990 prev_bline = bline;
991 }
992 }
993 if (!SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->included_files)) {
994 included_file *inc_file = SLIST_FIRST(&pp->included_files);
995 inc_file->lines_remaining += n * num_lines;
996 }
997 while (!SLIST_EMPTY(&lines)) {
998 buffered_line *bline = SLIST_FIRST(&lines);
999 SLIST_REMOVE_HEAD(&lines, next);
1000 yasm_xfree(bline->line);
1001 yasm_xfree(bline);
1002 }
1003 yasm_xfree(line);
1004 return 1;
1005 }
1006 if (n > 0) {
1007 buffered_line *bline = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(buffered_line));
1008 bline->line = line;
1009 bline->line_number = pp->next_line_number;
1010 if (prev_bline) {
1011 SLIST_INSERT_AFTER(prev_bline, bline, next);
1012 } else {
1013 SLIST_INSERT_HEAD(&lines, bline, next);
1014 }
1015 prev_bline = bline;
1016 } else {
1017 yasm_xfree(line);
1018 }
1019 line = read_line(pp);
1020 num_lines++;
1021 }
1022 yasm_linemap_set(pp->cur_lm, pp->in_filename, rept_start_output_line_number, rept_start_file_line_number, 0);
1023 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("rept without matching endr"));
1024 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, rept_start_output_line_number);
1025 return 0;
1026}
1027
1028static int eval_endr(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int unused)
1029{
1030 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("\".endr\" without \".rept\""));
1031 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
1032 return 0;
1033}
1034
1035/* Top-level line processing. */
1036
1037typedef int (*pp_fn0_t)(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int param);
1038typedef int (*pp_fn1_t)(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int param, const char *arg1);
1039typedef int (*pp_fn2_t)(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, int param, const char *arg1, const char *arg2);
1040
1041#define FN(f) ((pp_fn0_t) &(f))
1042
1043static void kill_comments(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, char *line)
1044{
1045 int next = 2;
1046 char *cstart;
1047
1048 skip_whitespace2(&line);
1049 if (*line == '#' || !strncmp(line, "//", 2)) {
1050 *line = '\0';
1051 return;
1052 }
1053
1054 if (pp->in_comment) {
1055 cstart = line;
1056 next = 0;
1057 } else {
1058 cstart = strstr(line, "/*");
1059 next = 2;
1060 }
1061
1062 while (cstart) {
1063 char *cend = strstr(cstart + next, "*/");
1064
1065 if (!cend) {
1066 *cstart = '\0';
1067 pp->in_comment = TRUE;
1068 return;
1069 }
1070
1071 memmove(cstart, cend + 2, strlen(cend + 2) + 1);
1072 pp->in_comment = FALSE;
1073 cstart = strstr(cstart, "/*");
1074 next = 2;
1075 }
1076}
1077
1078static int substitute_values(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, char **line_ptr)
1079{
1080 int changed = 0;
1081 char *line = *line_ptr;
1082 int line_length = strlen(line);
1083 struct tokenval tokval;
1084 expr_state prev_state = pp->expr;
1085
1086 gas_scan_init(pp, &tokval, line);
1087 while (gas_scan(pp, &tokval) != TOKEN_EOS) {
1088 if (tokval.t_type == TOKEN_ID) {
1089 yasm_symrec *rec = yasm_symtab_get(pp->defines, tokval.t_charptr);
1090 if (rec) {
1091 int cursor = pp->expr.string_cursor;
1092 int len = strlen(tokval.t_charptr);
1093 char value[64];
1094 int value_length = sprintf(value, "%ld", eval_expr(pp, tokval.t_charptr));
1095 int delta = value_length - len;
1096
1097 line_length += delta;
1098 if (delta > 0) {
1099 line = yasm_xrealloc(line, line_length + 1);
1100 }
1101 memmove(line + cursor - len + value_length, line + cursor, strlen(line + cursor) + 1);
1102 memcpy(line + cursor - len, value, value_length);
1103 pp->expr.string = line;
1104 pp->expr.string_cursor = cursor + delta;
1105 changed = 1;
1106 }
1107 yasm_xfree(pp->expr.symbol);
1108 pp->expr.symbol = NULL;
1109 }
1110 }
1111 gas_scan_cleanup(pp, &tokval);
1112 pp->expr = prev_state;
1113
1114 if (changed) {
1115 *line_ptr = line;
1116 }
1117
1118 return changed;
1119}
1120
1121static int process_line(yasm_preproc_gas *pp, char **line_ptr)
1122{
1123 macro_entry *macro;
1124 size_t i;
1125 char *line = *line_ptr;
1126 struct {
1127 const char *name;
1128 int nargs;
1129 pp_fn0_t fn;
1130 int param;
1131 } directives[] = {
1132 {"else", 0, FN(eval_else), 0},
1133 {"elseif", 1, FN(eval_elseif), 0},
1134 {"endif", 0, FN(eval_endif), 0},
1135 {"if", 1, FN(eval_if), 0},
1136 {"ifb", 1, FN(eval_ifb), 0},
1137 {"ifc", 1, FN(eval_ifc), 0},
1138 {"ifdef", 1, FN(eval_ifdef), 0},
1139 {"ifeq", 1, FN(eval_if), 1},
1140 {"ifeqs", 1, FN(eval_ifeqs), 0},
1141 {"ifge", 1, FN(eval_ifge), 0},
1142 {"ifgt", 1, FN(eval_ifgt), 0},
1143 {"ifle", 1, FN(eval_ifgt), 1},
1144 {"iflt", 1, FN(eval_ifge), 1},
1145 {"ifnb", 1, FN(eval_ifb), 1},
1146 {"ifnc", 1, FN(eval_ifc), 1},
1147 {"ifndef", 1, FN(eval_ifdef), 1},
1148 {"ifnotdef", 1, FN(eval_ifdef), 1},
1149 {"ifne", 1, FN(eval_if), 0},
1150 {"ifnes", 1, FN(eval_ifeqs), 1},
1151 {"include", 1, FN(eval_include), 0},
1152 {"set", 2, FN(eval_set), 1},
1153 {"equ", 2, FN(eval_set), 1},
1154 {"equiv", 2, FN(eval_set), 0},
1155 {"macro", 1, FN(eval_macro), 0},
1156 {"endm", 0, FN(eval_endm), 0},
1157 {"rept", 1, FN(eval_rept), 0},
1158 {"endr", 1, FN(eval_endr), 0},
1159 };
1160
1161 kill_comments(pp, line);
1162 skip_whitespace2(&line);
1163 if (*line == '\0') {
1164 return FALSE;
1165 }
1166
1167 /* See if this is a macro call. */
1168 STAILQ_FOREACH(macro, &pp->macros, next) {
1169 const char *remainder = starts_with(line, macro->name);
1170 if (remainder && (!*remainder || isspace(*remainder))) {
1171 skip_whitespace2(&line);
1172 expand_macro(pp, macro, remainder);
1173 return FALSE;
1174 }
1175 }
1176
1177 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(directives)/sizeof(directives[0]); i++) {
1178 char buf1[1024];
1179 const char *remainder = matches(line, directives[i].name);
1180
1181 if (remainder) {
1182 if (pp->skip_depth) {
1183 if (!strncmp("if", directives[i].name, 2)) {
1184 pp->skip_depth++;
1185 } else if (!strcmp("endif", directives[i].name)) {
1186 pp->skip_depth--;
1187 } else if (!strcmp("else", directives[i].name)) {
1188 if (pp->skip_depth == 1) {
1189 pp->skip_depth = 0;
1190 pp->depth++;
1191 }
1192 }
1193 return FALSE;
1194 } else if (directives[i].nargs == 0) {
1195 pp_fn0_t fn = (pp_fn0_t) directives[i].fn;
1196 pp->fatal_error = !fn(pp, directives[i].param);
1197 return FALSE;
1198 } else if (directives[i].nargs == 1) {
1199 pp_fn1_t fn = (pp_fn1_t) directives[i].fn;
1200 skip_whitespace(&remainder);
1201 pp->fatal_error = !fn(pp, directives[i].param, remainder);
1202 return FALSE;
1203 } else if (directives[i].nargs == 2) {
1204 remainder = get_arg(pp, remainder, buf1, sizeof(buf1));
1205 if (!remainder || !*remainder || !*buf1) {
1206 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("\".%s\" expects two arguments"), directives[i].name);
1207 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
1208 pp->fatal_error = 1;
1209 } else {
1210 pp_fn2_t fn = (pp_fn2_t) directives[i].fn;
1211 pp->fatal_error = !fn(pp, directives[i].param, buf1, remainder);
1212 }
1213 return FALSE;
1214 }
1215 }
1216 }
1217
1218 if (pp->skip_depth == 0) {
1219 substitute_values(pp, line_ptr);
1220 return TRUE;
1221 }
1222
1223 return FALSE;
1224}

1226/* Functions exported by the preprocessor. */
1227
1228static yasm_preproc *
1229gas_preproc_create(const char *in_filename, yasm_symtab *symtab,
1230 yasm_linemap *lm, yasm_errwarns *errwarns)
1231{
1232 FILE *f;
1233 yasm_preproc_gas *pp = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_preproc_gas));
1234
1235 if (strcmp(in_filename, "-") != 0) {
1236 f = fopen(in_filename, "r");
1237 if (!f) {
1238 yasm__fatal(N_("Could not open input file"));
1239 }
1240 } else {
1241 f = stdin;
1242 }
1243
1244 pp->preproc.module = &yasm_gas_LTX_preproc;
1245 pp->in = f;
1246 pp->in_filename = yasm__xstrdup(in_filename);
1247 pp->defines = yasm_symtab_create();
1248 SLIST_INIT(&pp->deferred_defines);
1249 yasm_symtab_set_case_sensitive(pp->defines, 1);
1250 pp->depth = 0;
1251 pp->skip_depth = 0;
1252 pp->in_comment = FALSE;
1253 SLIST_INIT(&pp->buffered_lines);
1254 SLIST_INIT(&pp->included_files);
1255 STAILQ_INIT(&pp->macros);
1256 pp->in_line_number = 0;
1257 pp->next_line_number = 0;
1258 pp->current_line_number = 0;
1259 pp->cur_lm = lm;
1260 pp->errwarns = errwarns;
1261 pp->fatal_error = 0;
1262 pp->detect_errors_only = 0;
1263
1264 return (yasm_preproc *) pp;
1265}
1266
1267static void
1268gas_preproc_destroy(yasm_preproc *preproc)
1269{
1270 yasm_preproc_gas *pp = (yasm_preproc_gas *) preproc;
1271 yasm_xfree(pp->in_filename);
1272 yasm_symtab_destroy(pp->defines);
1273 while (!SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->deferred_defines)) {
1274 deferred_define *def = SLIST_FIRST(&pp->deferred_defines);
1275 SLIST_REMOVE_HEAD(&pp->deferred_defines, next);
1276 yasm_xfree(def->name);
1277 yasm_xfree(def->value);
1278 yasm_xfree(def);
1279 }
1280 while (!SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->buffered_lines)) {
1281 buffered_line *bline = SLIST_FIRST(&pp->buffered_lines);
1282 SLIST_REMOVE_HEAD(&pp->buffered_lines, next);
1283 yasm_xfree(bline->line);
1284 yasm_xfree(bline);
1285 }
1286 while (!SLIST_EMPTY(&pp->included_files)) {
1287 included_file *inc_file = SLIST_FIRST(&pp->included_files);
1288 SLIST_REMOVE_HEAD(&pp->included_files, next);
1289 yasm_xfree(inc_file->filename);
1290 yasm_xfree(inc_file);
1291 }
1292 while (!STAILQ_EMPTY(&pp->macros)) {
1293 int i;
1294 macro_entry *macro = STAILQ_FIRST(&pp->macros);
1295 STAILQ_REMOVE_HEAD(&pp->macros, next);
1296 yasm_xfree(macro->name);
1297 for (i = 0; i < macro->num_params; i++)
1298 yasm_xfree(macro->params[i]);
1299 yasm_xfree(macro->params);
1300 for (i = 0; i < macro->num_lines; i++)
1301 yasm_xfree(macro->lines[i]);
1302 yasm_xfree(macro->lines);
1303 yasm_xfree(macro);
1304 }
1305 yasm_xfree(preproc);
1306}
1307
1308static char *
1309gas_preproc_get_line(yasm_preproc *preproc)
1310{
1311 yasm_preproc_gas *pp = (yasm_preproc_gas *)preproc;
1312 int done = FALSE;
1313 char *line = NULL;
1314
1315 pp->current_line_number++;
1316
1317 do {
1318 if (line != NULL) {
1319 yasm_xfree(line);
1320 }
1321 if (pp->fatal_error) {
1322 return NULL;
1323 }
1324 line = read_line(pp);
1325 if (line == NULL) {
1326 if (pp->in_comment) {
1327 yasm_linemap_set(pp->cur_lm, pp->in_filename, pp->current_line_number, pp->next_line_number, 0);
1328 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL, N_("end of file in comment"));
1329 yasm_errwarn_propagate(pp->errwarns, pp->current_line_number);
1330 pp->in_comment = FALSE;
1331 }
1332 return NULL;
1333 }
1334 done = process_line(pp, &line);
1335 } while (!done);
1336
1337 yasm_linemap_set(pp->cur_lm, pp->in_filename, pp->current_line_number, pp->next_line_number, 0);
1338
1339 return line;
1340}

1357static void
1358gas_preproc_predefine_macro(yasm_preproc *preproc, const char *macronameval)
1359{
1360 yasm_preproc_gas *pp = (yasm_preproc_gas *) preproc;
1361 const char *eq = strstr(macronameval, "=");
1362 char *name, *value;
1363 if (eq) {
1364 value = yasm__xstrdup(eq + 1);
1365 name = yasm_xmalloc(eq - macronameval + 1);
1366 memcpy(name, macronameval, eq - macronameval);
1367 name[eq - macronameval] = '\0';
1368 } else {
1369 name = yasm__xstrdup(macronameval);
1370 value = yasm__xstrdup("");
1371 }
1372 eval_set(pp, 1, name, value);
1373 yasm_xfree(name);
1374 yasm_xfree(value);
1375}
